    <node id="Details for dropout training experiments (page_number)">
      <data key="d0">Details for dropout training experiments (page_number)</data>
      <data key="d1">page_number</data>
      <data key="d2">This page outlines the experimental setup for dropout training using the MNIST dataset, detailing neural network architectures, dropout rates, and training methodologies. It connects the theoretical advantages of dropout discussed earlier to practical applications, providing insights into enhanced model performance and validation techniques.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-458082ea11f588d5307c1d9948dd5cd0</data>
      <data key="d4">[2012]_ImageNet_Classification_with_Deep_Convolutional_Neural_Networks.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1775047090</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Weight Update Formula with Dropout and Momentum (equation)">
      <data key="d0">Weight Update Formula with Dropout and Momentum (equation)</data>
      <data key="d1">equation</data>
      <data key="d2">This equation defines the weight update process in neural networks employing dropout and momentum during training, facilitating better convergence and reducing overfitting.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-3e1cdcaad914482ed7eaef787053cecd</data>
      <data key="d4">[2012]_ImageNet_Classification_with_Deep_Convolutional_Neural_Networks.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1775047090</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Weight Update Rule in Neural Networks (equation)">
      <data key="d0">Weight Update Rule in Neural Networks (equation)</data>
      <data key="d1">equation</data>
      <data key="d2">The equation describes how weight vectors are updated iteratively during neural network training, crucial for optimizing performance on tasks like digit classification, employing techniques such as dropout and gradient descent.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-dcbc540785e67a58a0e8941e3e7fcc4b</data>
      <data key="d4">[2012]_ImageNet_Classification_with_Deep_Convolutional_Neural_Networks.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1775047090</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Exponential Learning Rate Decay (equation)">
      <data key="d0">Exponential Learning Rate Decay (equation)</data>
      <data key="d1">equation</data>
      <data key="d2">Describes how the learning rate decreases exponentially over epochs to optimize training stability and efficiency in neural networks.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f3596177e754c3cf6c6a78b82e177b3c</data>
      <data key="d4">[2012]_ImageNet_Classification_with_Deep_Convolutional_Neural_Networks.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1775047090</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Momentum Adjustment Over Training Epochs (equation)">
      <data key="d0">Momentum Adjustment Over Training Epochs (equation)</data>
      <data key="d1">equation</data>
      <data key="d2">This equation defines the adjustment of the momentum parameter during neural network training, facilitating stable learning and effective convergence through dynamic changes based on epoch progression.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7b67c60a2d1480f70415891941c5701d</data>
      <data key="d4">[2012]_ImageNet_Classification_with_Deep_Convolutional_Neural_Networks.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1775047090</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Finetuning Pretrained Models using Dropout (page_number)">
      <data key="d0">Finetuning Pretrained Models using Dropout (page_number)</data>
      <data key="d1">page_number</data>
      <data key="d2">Page 8 delves into finetuning pretrained neural networks using dropout, comparing performance against standard backpropagation. It details two experimental setups: Dropout with Deep Belief Networks and Deep Boltzmann Machines, highlighting significant reductions in error rates, thereby underscoring the advantages of dropout in model training.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e95ae1a8da2db1bfc7469d545cf09f79</data>
      <data key="d4">[2012]_ImageNet_Classification_with_Deep_Convolutional_Neural_Networks.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1775047090</data>
    </node>
