      <data key="d0">Visualization of Learned Features from Neural Network Hidden Units (image)</data>
      <data key="d1">image</data>
      <data key="d2">This image shows a grid of visual features learned by the first layer of hidden units in a neural network using dropout on the MNIST dataset. Each patch represents abstract stroke-like features, highlighting the effectiveness of dropout in simplifying feature learning and improving generalization.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-1035a6950b7835c86bdb7de800e56b2d</data>
      <data key="d4">[2012]_ImageNet_Classification_with_Deep_Convolutional_Neural_Networks.pdf</data>
