    <node id="Datasets and Convolutional Neural Networks Overview (page_number)">
      <data key="d0">Datasets and Convolutional Neural Networks Overview (page_number)</data>
      <data key="d1">page_number</data>
      <data key="d2">Page 13 outlines the properties of key datasets utilized in machine learning, specifically the Tiny Images, CIFAR-10, and ImageNet collections. Additionally, it introduces the architecture and functionality of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), linking these concepts to training methodologies discussed on prior pages for enhanced model performance.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d0688d9219c58b5f05d5ac1233cc4e5f</data>
      <data key="d4">[2012]_ImageNet_Classification_with_Deep_Convolutional_Neural_Networks.pdf</data>
      <data key="d5">1775047090</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Convolutional Neural Networks Overview (page_number)">
      <data key="d0">Convolutional Neural Networks Overview (page_number)</data>
      <data key="d1">page_number</data>
      <data key="d2">This page provides an overview of Convolutional Neural Networks, detailing their structure, layer types, and how they reduce parameter count while enhancing generalization. It connects with Page 12's discussions on training methodologies and datasets like CIFAR-10 and ImageNet, forming a crucial part of the technical framework necessary for understanding advanced neural network applications.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-81b3ec07088578265f1923b93044fc3f</data>
