      <data key="d0">Mathematical Equation</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The Mathematical Equation encompasses the update rule for weights in a neural network, applying dropout during training to enhance convergence and stability.&lt;SEP&gt;The Mathematical Equation represents a fundamental iterative update rule for weight vectors in neural network training.&lt;SEP&gt;The Mathematical Equation represents a formula that is analyzed for its implications in neural network training, particularly in relation to learning rates.&lt;SEP&gt;The Mathematical Equation describes a dynamic parameter adjustment behavior over time within machine learning training procedures.&lt;SEP&gt;The Mathematical Equation represents a local response normalization operation within a convolutional neural network (CNN).</data>
