    <node id="Learning Rate">
      <data key="d0">Learning Rate</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Learning Rate is a hyperparameter in an optimization algorithm that determines the step size at each iteration while moving toward a minimum of a loss function.&lt;SEP&gt;Learning Rate is a hyperparameter that controls how much to change the model in response to the estimated error each time the model weights are updated.&lt;SEP&gt;The Learning Rate is a parameter that determines the step size at each iteration while moving toward a minimum of a loss function in neural networks.&lt;SEP&gt;Learning Rate indicates the speed at which a model learns during training, which can be adjusted based on momentum.&lt;SEP&gt;The Learning Rate (ε) is a hyperparameter that determines the size of the steps taken towards minimizing the loss function in training.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7b67c60a2d1480f70415891941c5701d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f3596177e754c3cf6c6a78b82e177b3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dcbc540785e67a58a0e8941e3e7fcc4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-334b34cebf9747d93cfba42c0f8c26c7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e1cdcaad914482ed7eaef787053cecd</data>
